strategy_reasoning: Devs love security panic jokes (leaking keys) and obsessive code cleanup (changing 19 files). Mixing high-stakes security fixes with trivial link unification creates that specific 'changelog whiplash' vibe.

images.prompt: A high-contrast, dramatic meme style illustration. A panicked cartoon server rack is sweating profusely, holding a sign that says 'I AM LEAKING API KEYS'. A superhero labeled 'PROXY WORKER' flies in and wraps the server in a thick steel blanket. Text at the bottom: 'Safety First (Finally)'.
images.description: Visualizing the move from client-side keys to the new Proxy Worker.

images.prompt: A close-up of a developer's face, looking absolutely deranged and sleep-deprived, eye twitching. Behind them is a matrix of screens, and every single screen displays the exact same Discord Invite URL. Text overlay: 'I changed the Discord link in 19 files. It is unified. I am at peace.'
images.description: Mocking the obsessive cleanup of the Discord links across the codebase.
